snippet.title: Amber Miller: Living Confidently Past Your Addictions and Fears
snippet.description:
Meet Amber Miller, a real estate investor, part-time X-ray and lab technician, and the founder of the Facebook group ‘A Life Not Wasted’. She has created a live program that gives women the tools they need to become confident and walk through the fear that holds them back so they can live an exciting and fulfilling life.

In this episode of Construct Your Life with Austin Linney, Amber narrates how she struggled with alcohol addiction for many years and the pivotal moment she decided to break that generational pattern. She talks about her personal development journey and how she’s working towards financial freedom.

Listen in to learn how you can transform your life when you put your mind to it and be open to the possibilities of a better future.

“When you work on yourself and when you learn what real self-love is, it radiates to everybody else.”- Amber [30:57]

What You Will Discover:
[2:59] Reaching out to like-minded people and making genuine connections.

[7:34] A life transformation: from an alcoholic to a writer.

[22:50] Deciding and writing a new narrative of who you are now, not who you used to be.

[29:38] The true meaning of self-love that radiates to everyone else.

[45:50] How to open up your mind to new ideas and opportunities.

[51:42] Making hard choices that will change your life.

Relevant Links:
Facebook Group: https://www.facebook.com/groups/217125266224956
Book Mentioned: The Total Money Makeover by Dave Ramsey

#podcast
